# 1:1 — Leadership (Weekly)

## Etiquette & Guidelines
- **Reference**: See `../meeting-etiquette-guidelines.md.tmpl` for comprehensive meeting standards
- **Topics to Cover**: Focus on priorities, progress, risks, decisions, and feedback
- **Topics to Avoid**: Sensitive topics (religion, politics, personal compensation, gossip)
- **Communication**: Keep professional, solution-focused, and transparent
- **Preparation**: Use MoSCoW checklist and update shared doc by EOD prior day

## How to Set Up
- **Reference**: See `../meeting-invitation-templates.md.tmpl` for leadership-specific invitation templates
- **Timing**: Schedule 3-5 days in advance, provide 2-3 time options
- **Format**: Professional email with clear agenda and shared document link
- **Prep Sharing**: Include "Update doc with progress, risks, and decisions by EOD prior day" in calendar invite

## Objectives
- Align on outcomes and priorities; unblock decisions; exchange feedback.

## Agenda (30–45m)
- Wins and progress since last time
- Top 3 priorities this week
- Risks/blockers and asks
- Decisions needed (options → recommendation)
- Feedback both ways
- Metrics snapshot (vs. targets)
- Admin/logistics

## Prep (async)
- **Reference**: Use `../moscow-meeting-prep-checklist.md.tmpl` for comprehensive preparation
- **Must Have**: Update shared doc with progress, risks, and decisions by EOD prior day
- **Should Have**: Link relevant dashboards/PRDs, prepare metrics snapshot
- **Could Have**: Prepare visual progress reports, anticipate leadership questions
- **Won't Have**: Personal topics, unprepared speculation, non-work discussions
- **Additional**: Update doc with progress, risks, and decisions by EOD prior day; link relevant dashboards/PRDs

